tps://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/17210/56/172105665_0:27:501:308_1920x0_80_0_0_163bb7a38c28e53888f056e2e509d571.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Flickr /<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/prinsrichard/2964325106/" title="理查德">理查德</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">斯韦特兰娜·埃基缅科</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_svetlana_ekimenko/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:s.ekimenko@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">2008年的一项调查显示，美国坚定信仰上帝的人数超过60%。然而，最近的一项民意调查显示，坚定信仰的人数有所下降。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">新发现显示，只有大约一半的美国人坚信上帝的存在。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据芝加哥大学研究机构<a href="https://gss.norc.org/Documents/codebook/GSS%202022%20Codebook.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">NORC 发布的</a>2022 年<em>综合社会调查</em>，34% 的美国人<strong>甚至从未跨过教堂的门槛</strong>。它补充说，这个数字是五年来调查中的最高记录。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据自 2008 年以来的调查，超过 60% 的人坚定不移地信仰上帝，但现在美国正面临着越来越多的非宗教人口。学者们说，教会成员、出勤率和对上帝的信仰都在下降。早些年的同一项<em>综合社会调查</em>发现，到 2021 年，29% 的美国人没有宗教信仰。这一比例高于 1972 年不信奉任何宗教的人数的 5%。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该调查自 1972 年以来一直由 NORC 进行。根据该网站，其目标是“监测社会变化并研究美国社会日益复杂的情况”，观察“近年来公众的态度和观点可能发生了怎样的变化”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110534214" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110534334_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_a55b69a2bd0713738c9c8791878ecd7e.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110534316" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/losing-their-religion-only-50-of-americans-believe-in-god-1110534214.html?share-img=1110534316"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / JASON CONNOLLY</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">社区成员聚集在美国万灵一神论教会。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="afp" alt="Community members gather at the All Souls Unitarian Church in US. - Sputnik International, 1920, 23.05.2023" title="社区成员聚集在美国的 All Souls Unitarian 教会。" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110534334_0:0:3072:2048_1920x0_80_0_0_aa66605cef715e9ca23e67eba816ff0c.jpg" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%221280%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1280" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110534334_0:0:3072:2048_640x0_80_0_0_d6c08e121d417a011e2ab44629857d70.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110534334_0:0:3072:2048_1280x0_80_0_0_84093035fd73229f222d72a1ee5e20b3.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110534334_0:0:3072:2048_1920x0_80_0_0_aa66605cef715e9ca23e67eba816ff0c.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet="">社区成员聚集在美国的 All Souls Unitarian 教会。 </div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / 杰森·康诺利</div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">有多少美国人是无神论者？</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">另一份报告似乎证实了这些关于美国宗教的调查结果。 <a href="https://www.prri.org/research/religion-and-congregations-in-a-time-of-social-and-political-upheaval/?utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter_axiosam&amp;stream=top" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">27% 的美国人</a><strong>声称在 2022 年没有宗教信仰</strong>——高于 2006 年的 16%。至于宗教的重要性，只有 16% 的美国人表示这是他们生活中最重要的事情。与此同时，早在 2013 年，接受调查的美国人<strong>更有可能说宗教是他们生活中最重要的事情</strong>(20%) 或<strong>许多重要事情之一</strong>(43%)。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110534214" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110537110_0:0:599:658_1440x900_80_0_1_ba0a55d382d1ef825e767bbf7557be80.png?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110537092" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/losing-their-religion-only-50-of-americans-believe-in-god-1110534214.html?share-img=1110537092"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 照片： <a href="https://www.prri.org/research/religion-and-congregations-in-a-time-of-social-and-political-upheaval/?utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter_axiosam&amp;stream=top" title="公共宗教研究所（PRRI），">公共宗教研究所 (PRRI)，</a> /社会和政治动荡时期的宗教和会众</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">公共宗教研究所 (PRRI) 追踪美国宗教重要性的报告截图。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Screenshot of report from the Public Religion Research Institute (PRRI) tracking importance of Religion in the United States. - Sputnik International, 1920, 23.05.2023" title="公共宗教研究所 (PRRI) 追踪美国宗教重要性的报告截图。" class="m-vertical lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110537110_0:0:599:658_1920x0_80_0_0_de16d78dadf3b78eb2add45b4d746f50.png" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%222109%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="2109" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110537110_0:0:599:658_640x0_80_0_0_e7e975df4b96831d3fcb5d4ed579f575.png 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110537110_0:0:599:658_1280x0_80_0_0_b029beb9157202e1eb4b2a3c5f3d0103.png 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/17/1110537110_0:0:599:658_1920x0_80_0_0_de16d78dadf3b78eb2add45b4d746f50.png 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet="">公共宗教研究所 (PRRI) 追踪美国宗教重要性的报告截图。 </div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片： <a href="https://www.prri.org/research/religion-and-congregations-in-a-time-of-social-and-political-upheaval/?utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter_axiosam&amp;stream=top" title="公共宗教研究所（PRRI），">公共宗教研究所 (PRRI)，</a> / 社会和政治动荡时期的宗教和会众</div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据研究人员称，美国的教会会众一直在减少。 <a href="https://research.lifeway.com/2021/05/25/protestant-church-closures-outpace-openings-in-u-s/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">根据 Lifeway Research 的数据</a>，2019 年约有 4,500 座新教教堂关闭，约有 3,000 座新教堂开放。根据 Lifeway 的调查，2017 年，每 10 名 18 至 22 岁的年轻人中，有 7 名以前定期去教堂的人现在不再去教堂了。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “年轻一代只是觉得他们在教会环境中没有被接受，或者他们的一些选择没有被接受，”Lifeway Research 的斯科特麦康奈尔说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110534214" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/losing-their-religion-only-50-of-americans-believe-in-god-1110534214.html?share-block=1110537708" data-title="&quot;The younger generation just doesn’t feel like they’re being accepted in a church environment or some of their choices aren’t being accepted,&quot; Scott McConnell, of Lifeway Research, stated."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据<em>美国生活调查中心的</em>数据，一些学者认为，信仰下降的趋势更多是世代相传的趋势，因为调查显示，随着年龄越来越小，声称没有宗教信仰的美国人的比例逐渐上升。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 23 May 2023 11:56:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230523/losing-their-religion-only-50-of-americans-believe-in-god-1110534214.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230523/losing-their-religion-only-50-of-americans-believe-in-god-1110534214.html<category>美洲</category><category>宗教</category><category>我们</category><category>上帝</category><category>芝加哥大学</category><category>美国人</category><category>社会</category><category>教会</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[VTB Chairman: Yuan to Replace Dollar as Main Reserve Currency in Future]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110534045" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110262742_0:0:2730:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_c2cf2a68611306f21d2cd8e40b9ab412.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110262724" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/vtb-chairman-yuan-to-replace-dollar-as-main-reserve-currency-in-future-1110534045.html?share-img=1110262724"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / STR</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2015 年 8 月 14 日，在中国中部湖北省宜昌的一张桌子上可以看到人民币纸币和美元</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="Yuan banknotes and US dollars are seen on a table in Yichang, central China's Hubei province on August 14, 2015 - Sputnik International, 1920, 23.05.2023" title="2015 年 8 月 14 日，在中国中部湖北省宜昌市的一张桌子上可以看到人民币纸币和美元" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110262742_0:257:2730:1793_1920x0_80_0_0_5296071299a206aeb7ba589eae4acc2c.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110262742_0:257:2730:1793_640x0_80_0_0_c0113a15f6ab5c9b7020234bd42c70f8.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110262742_0:257:2730:1793_1280x0_80_0_0_e24123ed5feacc1e722b8177a47c532d.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110262742_0:257:2730:1793_1920x0_80_0_0_5296071299a206aeb7ba589eae4acc2c.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> ©<a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">法新社 2023</a> / STR </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">此前，俄罗斯副外长安德烈·鲁坚科表示，近年来俄中两国结算中本国货币的份额一直在增​​长，这一进程在 2022 年将显着加快。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">俄罗斯VTB银行行长安德烈·科斯廷表示，未来10年<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/bolivia-advances-in-replacing-dollar-with-yuan-for-trade-with-china-1110523311.html" target="_blank">人民币</a>可能取代美元成为世界储备和结算货币。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “中国现在是世界第二大经济体，而且很快就会成为第一大经济体。有充分的理由预计， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230331/not-by-yuan-alone-whole-set-of-national-currencies-to-deep-six-us-dollar-dominance--1109012015.html" target="_blank">人民币</a>最早在下一个十年内就会取代美元成为世界主要的储备和结算货币。事实上，俄罗斯中央银行已经将其储备投资于人民币，俄罗斯和中国之间超过 70% 的贸易额是用人民币和卢布结算的，”科斯廷在上海举行的俄中商业论坛上说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110534045" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/vtb-chairman-yuan-to-replace-dollar-as-main-reserve-currency-in-future-1110534045.html?share-block=1110534047" data-title="&amp;quot;China is now the world&amp;#x27;s second-largest economy and will soon become the first. There is every reason to expect that the Chinese yuan will replace the US dollar as the world&amp;#x27;s main reserve and settlement currency as early as the next decade. In fact, the Central Bank of Russia is already investing its reserves in yuan, and more than 70 percent of trade turnover between Russia and China is settled in yuan together with the ruble,&amp;quot; Kostin said at the Russian-Chinese business forum in Shanghai."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据他介绍，主导数十年的货币和金融体系确保了美国及其西方盟友的霸权地位，美元和欧元占全球结算的四分之三。科斯汀补充说，美元是世界主要储备货币，但在宣布对俄罗斯和中国采取遏制措施后，西方国家，尤其是美国，一直在积极使用其货币作为武器。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">今年3月，俄罗斯总统普京表示，有必要推动俄中两国以本国货币相互结算的做法。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">近几个月来，俄罗斯一直在加强与中国的经济合作，并采用人民币进行贸易。 4 月初，人民币取代美元成为俄罗斯交易量最大的货币，中国货币继续渗透到世界其他许多市场。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 23 May 2023 11:40:16 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230523/vtb-chairman-yuan-to-replace-dollar-as-main-reserve-currency-in-future-1110534045.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230523/vtb-chairman-yuan-to-replace-dollar-as-main-reserve-currency-in-future-1110534045.html<category>经济</category><category>安德烈科斯汀</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>中国</category><category>外贸银行</category><category>美元</category><category>元</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[British Ex-PM Johnson in Texas to Urge Republicans to Keep Arming Ukraine]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110534729" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/06/12/1096425819_0:0:2318:1513_1440x900_80_0_1_6cd6962ec6f14a6aa06e7da54568c0c3.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1096425802" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/british-ex-pm-johnson-in-texas-to-urge-republicans-to-keep-arming-ukraine-1110534729.html?share-img=1096425802"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"><span class="photoview__copyright"></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">在这张由乌克兰总统新闻办公室提供的图片中，乌克兰总统沃洛德米尔·泽伦斯基（右）和英国首相鲍里斯·约翰逊于 2022 年 6 月 17 日星期五在乌克兰基辅举行会议。（乌克兰总统新闻办公室来自美联社）</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="In this image provided by the Ukrainian Presidential Press Office, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy, right, and Britain's Prime Minister Boris Johnson, ahead of their meeting in Kyiv, Ukraine, Friday, June 17, 2022. (Ukrainian Presidential Press Office via AP) - Sputnik International, 1920, 23.05.2023" title="在这张由乌克兰总统新闻办公室提供的图片中，乌克兰总统沃洛德米尔·泽伦斯基（右）和英国首相鲍里斯·约翰逊于 2022 年 6 月 17 日星期五在乌克兰基辅举行会议。（乌克兰总统新闻办公室来自美联社）" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/06/12/1096425819_0:0:2319:1304_1920x0_80_0_0_449a604417ea7a246d5fbb1f09d2179a.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/06/12/1096425819_0:0:2319:1304_640x0_80_0_0_0657ffb130087efe377dabf354eedeae.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/06/12/1096425819_0:0:2319:1304_1280x0_80_0_0_50dd4946af738682c18b3adad8cc0b7b.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/06/12/1096425819_0:0:2319:1304_1920x0_80_0_0_449a604417ea7a246d5fbb1f09d2179a.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="James Tweedie - Sputnik International" title="詹姆斯·特威迪" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1c/1080307270_0:3:397:400_100x100_80_0_0_7777393b9b18802f2e3c5eaa9cbcc612.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">詹姆斯·特威迪</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_tweedie_james/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:j.tweedie@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">鲍里斯约翰逊在北约与俄罗斯在乌克兰的代理人冲突中发挥了核心作用。 2022 年 4 月，他说服弗拉基米尔·泽伦斯基总统退出和平协议。他还说服其他欧洲领导人武装基辅并制裁莫斯科。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">英国前首相<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/ukraines-former-pm-reveals-how-zelensky-transformed-from-stage-actor-to-american-puppet-1110487778.html" target="_blank">鲍里斯·约翰逊</a>敦促美国共和党人继续支持民主党总统乔·拜登向乌克兰提供武器。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位前总理飞往美国得克萨斯州，向大约两打孤星州的顶级保守派政治家、商人和竞选捐助者发表讲话。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “我只是敦促大家坚持下去。从长远来看，它会带来巨大的回报，”约翰逊在集会上说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110534729" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/british-ex-pm-johnson-in-texas-to-urge-republicans-to-keep-arming-ukraine-1110534729.html?share-block=1110535227" data-title="&amp;quot;I just urge you all to stick with it. It will pay off massively in the long run,&amp;quot; Johnson told the gathering."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “你支持正确的马。乌克兰要赢了。他们将打败普京，”他坚称，尽管当天有消息称俄罗斯军队已经解放了顿巴斯的重要城市阿尔捷莫夫斯克。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国国会的共和党人目前与民主党政府陷入僵局，民主党政府坚称必须将其“债务上限”借款限额从 1.1 万亿美元提高到 1.5 万亿美元，以支付年度预算中批准的支出。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>更激进的共和党代表和参议员公开反对向基辅提供至少 480 亿美元的军事援助，而美国国内面临多重危机，一些人指责政府为拜登“洗钱”，拜登的儿子亨特成为乌克兰天然气公司 Burisma 的高管。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但这位八十多岁的总统发誓，即使联邦政府被迫关闭，武器供应仍将继续。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">约翰逊此行是由欧洲政策分析中心 (CEPA) 组织的，这是一个跨党派、亲乌克兰的华盛顿游说团体。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们想在华盛顿以外的地方——我们都生活在泡沫中——真正把它带到中心地带，带到得克萨斯州这样的地方，以获得对乌克兰的更多支持，并向那些持怀疑态度的人证明这一点。这种支持，”CEPA 出生于乌克兰的总裁兼首席执行官 Alina Polyakova 说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110534729" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/british-ex-pm-johnson-in-texas-to-urge-republicans-to-keep-arming-ukraine-1110534729.html?share-block=1110535470" data-title="&quot;We wanted to make that case outside of Washington — where we all live in a bubble — and to really take it to the heartland, to places like Texas, to get more support for Ukraine, and make the case to people who are sceptical about that support,&quot; said CEPA's Ukrainian-born president and CEO Alina Polyakova."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">她补充说，约翰逊“在共和党基础中享有很高的信誉”，因为美国前总统唐纳德特朗普“在他担任总统时对他说了很多好话。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在乌克兰与俄罗斯的冲突中，约翰逊一直是乌克兰大西洋东岸最坚定的支持者之一。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2022 年 4 月上旬，他飞往基辅，敦促乌克兰总统沃洛德米尔·泽连斯基中断与俄罗斯的和平谈判，该谈判即将在土耳其和以色列的斡旋下达成和平协议。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他还说服欧盟最大的三个经济体法国、 <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230205/putin-never-threatened-me-or-germany-olaf-scholz-says-in-wake-of-boris-johnsons-missile-claims-1106988011.html" target="_blank">德国</a>和意大利的领导人对俄罗斯实施经济制裁，这损害了他们国家的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20221123/johnson-admits-sound-economic-reasons-for-wanting-ukraine-to-surrender-1104575858.html" target="_blank">经济利益。</a></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">约翰逊于 2022 年夏天被迫辞职，此前他几个月前任命他为副首席党鞭的克里斯·平彻 (Chris Pincher) 在伦敦西区一家豪华的私人会员俱乐部摸索了一名保守党议员。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这促使当时的财政大臣 Rishi Sunak 带领他的内阁大规模罢工。约翰逊的声誉已经因早期丑闻而受损，例如<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230321/boris-johnson-admits-misleading-parliament-on-partygate-in-good-faith---committee-1108665410.html" target="_blank">“派对门”</a>以及他以牺牲保守党资金为代价对首相在唐宁街的官邸进行昂贵的整修。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他的继任者<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20221101/moscow-wants-answers-over-truss-alleged-its-done-sms-to-blinken-moments-after-nord-stream-blasts-1102909463.html" target="_blank">、与莫斯科对抗的另一位支持者利兹·特拉斯</a>在唐宁街任职仅六周后就辞职，由曾两度<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230208/beggar-on-the-streets-of-london-zelenskys-surprise-uk-visit--video-1107080041.html" target="_blank">招待</a>泽伦斯基的苏纳克接任。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 23 May 2023 11:38:43 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230523/british-ex-pm-johnson-in-texas-to-urge-republicans-to-keep-arming-ukraine-1110534729.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230523/british-ex-pm-johnson-in-texas-to-urge-republicans-to-keep-arming-ukraine-1110534729.html<category>世界</category><category>鲍里斯约翰逊</category><category>得克萨斯州</category><category>我们</category><category>英国</category><category>英国</category><category>大不列颠</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>共和党</category><category>共和党人</category><category>美国国会</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>沃洛德米尔·泽伦斯基</category><category>欧洲政策分析中心 (CEPA)</category><category>共和党人</category></item></channel></rss>